<body>
    <h1>Steps in designing an API</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <ul>
<li>Handover from Architect which will contain APIs, operations and resourc=
es identified from <a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display=
/mesh/Decomposing+my+solution+into+API%27s" rel=3D"nofollow">solutioning</a=
></li>
<li>Get the latest copy of the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westp=
ac.com.au/display/mesh/The+Swagger+Golden+Template" rel=3D"nofollow">golden=
 swagger specification</a>&nbsp;and overwrite the swagger.yaml file provide=
d in the project archetype.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>Define the happy path response structure<br>
<ul>
<li>use the appropriate http 2xx response code&nbsp;from the list of approv=
ed Westpac Mesh response codes</li>
<li>Define the primary entities, and related entities where applicable</li>
<li>Use the<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/display/mesh/Co=
mmon+Data+Types" rel=3D"nofollow"> common data types</a></li>
<li>Name the fields appropriately and declare the correct data type<br>
<ul>
<li>Field naming - use provider definitions and/or existing services as a g=
uide, clearly describe their purpose, prefer business terminology over tech=
nical, no abbreviations (acronyms are ok)</li>
<li>Data types - use format qualifier where appropriate, decimal amounts to=
 use string</li>
</ul></li>
<li>use enums where appropriate - eg. where provider values are static, don=
't use for reference data<br>
<ul>
<li>name enum values in business terms not codes</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Indicate required fields</li>
<li>Provide default values for optional request fields where appropriate (e=
g. pageSize)</li>
<li>Provide field value constraints where appropriate (minLength, maxLength=
, pattern, minimum, maximum)</li>
<li>Provide a meaningful description for each field</li>
<li>Check cardinality of each entity</li>
<li>Use composition and polymorphism for fields where appropriate</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Input parameters - query parameter (GET, DELETE) or body (POST, PUT) <b=
r>
<ul>
<li>Use common parameters where appropriate (eg. sort, pageKey)</li>
<li>When defining filter parameters ensure that the parameter names match t=
he equivalent fields in the response body</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Unhappy path response codes and error codes, including partial success =
if applicable. Refer: <a href=3D"/display/MESH/API+Error+Handling">API Erro=
r Handling</a><br>
<ul>
<li>Use the appropriate http 4xx or 5xx response code from the list of appr=
oved Westpac Mesh response codes</li>
<li>Define the error codes and document in Swagger using the format prescri=
bed in the golden swagger template</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Include example values for responses<br>
<ul>
<li>Be careful that you include all possible fields in the response otherwi=
se they will be omitted when viewed in Swagger Editor</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Complete Info object fields<br>
<ul>
<li>Ensure API description contains sufficient detail for a potential consu=
mer of the API to decide if it might be suitable for their use case - inclu=
de a description for each operation supported</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Check Swagger file against the<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac=
.com.au/display/mesh/Mandatory+Swagger+Spec+Checklist" rel=3D"nofollow"> ma=
ndatory checklist</a></li>
<li>Create a new page for the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpa=
c.com.au/display/MESH/API+Design+Template" rel=3D"nofollow">detailed design=
 document </a>and update the field x-detailedTechnicalDesignURL&nbsp;in the=
 Swagger Spec</li>
<li>Get spec peer reviewed and then reviewed by Chapter Lead</li>
<li>Complete the&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au/disp=
lay/MESH/API+Design+Template" rel=3D"nofollow">detailed design document</a>=
</li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
